To request data, send a message to the WebSocket with the `GET_DATA` event with each module to receive data from.

```json
{
    "id": "abc123",
    "token": "abc123",
    "event": "GET_DATA",
    "data": {
        "modules": ["system"]
    }
}
```

To register as a listener, connect to the WebSocket at `/api/websocket` and send a message with the event `REGISTER_DATA_LISTENER` including each module you want to subscribe to.

```json
{
    "id": "abc123",
    "token": "abc123",
    "event": "REGISTER_DATA_LISTENER",
    "data": { "modules": ["cpu", "memory", "system"] }
}
```

Actions and values can be found [here](https://github.com/timmo001/system-bridge-models/blob/master/systembridgemodels/media_control.py)

```json
{
    "id": "abc123",
    "token": "abc123",
    "event": "MEDIA_CONTROL",
    "data": {
        "action": "PAUSE",
        "value": null
    }
}
```
